      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence study performed on three mesh densities (coarse: ~45k elements, medium: ~120k elements, fine: ~310k elements). Richardson extrapolation applied to stiffness and yield force QoIs. Grid convergence index (GCI) for medium mesh: 1.8% for stiffness, 2.3% for yield force — both below the 5% threshold. Production mesh uses medium density with local refinement at screw-rod interface and thread root stress concentration regions.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/discretization-error",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "GCI for production mesh must be < 5% for all primary QoIs. Richardson extrapolation must be applied across at least three mesh densities with refinement ratio ≥ 1.3. Gradation 3 requires documented GCI calculation with extrapolated reference values."
