      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "Linear elastic isotropic material model used for Ti-6Al-4V screw and CoCr rod, consistent with sub-yield loading regime for stiffness QoI. Bilinear isotropic hardening (BISO) used for yield force and post-yield QoIs, with tangent modulus calibrated from coupon tensile tests (n=5 per material lot). UHMWPE block modeled as linear elastic with modulus from compressive characterization. Coulomb friction contact (μ=0.15) at screw-rod and fixture interfaces. Model form choices documented in Modeling Report MR-2024-NC-001.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/model-form",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "Material model must capture dominant deformation mechanisms for each QoI. Contact model must represent physical interface behavior. Model form choices must be documented with physical justification. Gradation 2 requires documented model form selection rationale."
